Sugar Futures May Gain Next Week on Rising Demand, Survey Says

-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m   a n d   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a
-- 
2011-08-18T23:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/sugar-futures-may-gain-next-week-on-rising-demand-survey-says.html
Raw sugar may advance next week on
signs of rising global demand.  Five of nine traders, analysts and brokers surveyed by
Bloomberg News said raw sugar in  New York  would rise. Two
forecast a fall, and two were neutral. Before today, futures for
October delivery rose 4.6 percent this week to 29.12 cents a
pound on ICE Futures U.S.  Six respondents said refined sugar on London’s NYSE Liffe
would gain. Two expected a slide. One said prices would be
steady. Futures for October delivery rose 3 percent this week
through yesterday to $765.80 a metric ton.  Five of eight respondents said refined sugar’s premium over
raw would widen. Two said it would narrow, and one was neutral.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Justin Doom in New York at 
